    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the implementation plan for `uv cache stats`:\n\n## What the plan covers\n\n**8 files across 4 crates**, all modelled on how `uv cache size` was wired in:\n\n| File | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs` | Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` preview feature flag |\n| `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` | Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant + `StatsArgs` struct with `--human/-H` |\n| `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` | **New file** — core implementation |\n| `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs` | Export + module declaration |\n| `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` | Dispatch match arm |\n| `crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs` | `cache_stats()` builder + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter |\n| `crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs` | **New file** — 3 integration tests |\n| `crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs` | Register test module |\n\n## Key implementation decisions\n\n- **All 11 buckets shown**, including `CacheBucket::Python` which is intentionally excluded from `CacheBucket::iter()` (that iterator is for per-package removal operations, not directory enumeration).\n- **Per-bucket sizing** uses `diskus::DiskUsage` (same crate as `cache_size`) on each bucket's path, returning 0 for directories that don't exist yet.\n- **Column alignment** is computed dynamically — `environments-v2:` is the longest label at 16 chars, so all rows are padded to that width.\n- **`--human` formatting** mirrors the pattern in `cache_clean.rs`: values below 1024 bytes print as `\"NB\"`, above use `human_readable_bytes()` from `uv-console`.\n- **Preview guard** follows the exact `CacheSize` pattern — warns if `--preview` isn't passed, but still executes.",
